Maj Gen '''Ian Deetlefs''' (Rtd) {{Post-nominals|country = ZAR|SSAS|PG|SM|JCD}} served in the South African Army's Reserve Force from 1965{{ndash}}2003. He became the first ''Chief of Defence Reserves'' of the [[South African National Defence Force]] in 1997.<ref name=LinkedIn>{{cite web|title=Ian Deetlefs - LinkedIn|url=https://www.linkedin.com/pub/ian-deetlefs/13/423/70|website=linkedin.com|accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref> He retired from the SANDF in 2003 and was succeeded by Maj Gen [[Roy Anderson (South Africa)|R.C. Andersen]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Masilela |first1=J.B. |title=Department of Defence Annual Report 2003-2004 |date=2004 |publisher=Formeset Printers |location=Cape |isbn=0621352543 |page=53 |url=http://www.dod.mil.za/documents/annualreports/AnnualReport2004.pdf |accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref>

